{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by initiating partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a long prison sentence is disproportionate to the amount stolen and does not account for the defendant's lack of criminal history. The outburst from the courtroom spectator is irrelevant to the legal merits of the case and has been disregarded. A sentence of 6 months is sufficient to address the punitive aspects of the crime while allowing for the focus to remain on full restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
